# VPS Supabase backend (mandatory)

**FuelBot backend = self-hosted Supabase on VPS.** Not Supabase Cloud.

| What | URL |
|------|-----|
| **API** | `https://fuelbot.lucas-dev-server.tech` |
| **Studio** | `https://studio.fuelbot.lucas-dev-server.tech` |

## Never do this

- Do **not** use `*.supabase.co`, project ref `feenwusofmhnpuahekvu`, or Supabase Cloud Dashboard
- Do **not** use Supabase Cloud MCP (`mcp.supabase.com`) or ask the user to `supabase db push` to cloud
- Do **not** assume SSH tunnels — the API is public HTTPS

Read **[AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md)** and **[docs/SUPABASE_SETUP.md](../../docs/SUPABASE_SETUP.md)** first for DB/backend work.

## Apply migrations (VPS only)

1. SQL files in `supabase/migrations/`
2. Apply via **Studio SQL editor** (paste + run), **or**
3. `POST {VITE_SUPABASE_URL}/pg/query` with body `{ "query": "<sql>" }` and header `Authorization: Bearer $SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` (local `.env.local` only — AI should run this, not ask the user to paste SQL unless they prefer Studio)

## Connections

| Task | Use |
|------|-----|
| DDL / inspect tables / ad-hoc SQL | Studio or `/pg/query` (service role, local) |
| React app auth + RLS queries | `VITE_SUPABASE_URL` + `VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` |
| Import scripts, bypass RLS | Local `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` |
| Deploy frontend | Vercel with same `VITE_SUPABASE_*` |

Run `npm run audit:supabase` to confirm env points at the VPS API URL.
